<br>
Day One:<br>
<br>
Guild A says, &quot;hey I think this should be a new rule&quot;<br>
<br>
Guild A is flamed by Guild B.  Guild B is flamed by Guild C.  Guild D defends Guild B.  We all flame each other some more and bring up every nasty thing we have ever said and/or done to every other guild in the history of the Druzzil Ro server.  We quote things over one year old.  We re-kindle hatreds over one year old.  We point fingers and say you started it.  The insults get nasty and more personal.  Baramos and Andaas turn psychoanalyist and revert to their inner child.  A wheeeeeee FU post emerges.  I pocket the gnomes.  48 hours or so pass and it becomes funny - in a sick, twisted and embarrassing way.  <br>
<br>
Then we revert back to the discussion.  On a good day, the flames don't start immediately back up.<br>
<br>
It sucks and its stressful and it's increased the sale of Advil in every IGB reps hometown by 200%.  No in-game issue is ever as painful as an IGB discussion =P<br>
<br>
And I probably still would dump a beer on Quintall... if he didn't dump his on me first. <p>Sirensa the Vicar<br>
